comments.body:
@mheon 
Ok the shm is false alarm. It is a tmpfs, so that should be in memory. free only shows the usage in the buffer category, and somehow I was expecting to see the mount somewhere in /dev/shm on the host, not in /var/lib... but that was silly of me... 

When it comes to buildah, the `podman build` man page doesn't mention buidah at all in the description. I think it's unclear right now whether the intended workflow is use buildah for building, podman for running (in which case the existence of podman build is questionable) or whether the idea is that podman is the public interface and buildah is like a porcelain command.
